reviewText: The graphics are as beautiful as the ones of the first DVD. The difference is that the songs are not as catchy. My daughter likes most of the songs, but is not as interested in it as the first one. I definitely love "Head Shoulders Knees and Toes," "Colors of the Rainbow," "If You're Happy and You Know It," "Eat 'Em All Up," and "If All the Little Raindrops." I'd recommend that parents take sneak previews of the DVD on youtube before buying it.
summary: Good, but not as great as the first

reviewText: I originally was hearing a sound distortion on this DVD in the voice tracks. The GiggleBellies folks were awesome and corresponded with me to get more information, and they replaced the DVD and send an envelope to reclaim the old one. After a lot of comparative examination, I found that the original played perfectly on my laptop, and had the greatest distortion on my LG television that had ClearVoice II technology (voice enhancement). I am guessing the distortion on the other two televisions may have been an "unemphasized" feature of those TV's to enhance voices...but I found I could turn off the ClearVoice II and the music and voice tracks were true and fun. I really appreciated the excellent service and care the GiggleBellies folks took to address my issue and look forward to their next Volumes! This 2nd Vol also features the endless loop of play...which is handy for some parents-- though I enjoy my baby "announcing" with her slight whimper that the last song is playing and I choose to restart it for her or to give her something different for variety.
